==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blindworm
<hw>Blind"worm`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small, burrowing, snakelike, limbless lizard (<spn>Anguis
fragilis</spn>), with minute eyes, popularly believed to be blind; the
slowworm; -- formerly a name for the adder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Newts and <qex>blindworms</qex> do no wrong.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>blini</ent>⟦br⟧
